19/10/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Russian Prime Minister Mikhail Fradkov is making a two-day visit to Bulgaria that is expected to boost bilateral co-operation in the field of industry.
A total of five agreements regulating co-operation in the energy, trade and transport sectors will be sealed.
The agenda also includes major energy projects, such as the construction of a second nuclear power plant in Bulgaria.
(Sega, bTV, ITAR-TASS - 19/10/04)
